    "id" : 11,
    "name" : "Wild Blueberries Lesson 2 Glossary",
    "json" : "{\"askForUserDefinition\":false,\"autoShowMediaInPopup\":true,\"showSideBar\":true,\"enableStudentRecording\":false,\"definitions\":[{\"word\":\"bumble bees\",\"definition\":\"Large, fuzzy bees that are well adapted to flying in Maine’s cool climate. Bumble bees are very important to wild blueberry production because of their highly efficient buzz pollination technique.\"},{\"word\":\"native bees\",\"definition\":\"Bees originally from the place where they live.\"},{\"word\":\"pollination\",\"definition\":\"Pollination is an important part of the life cycle of wild blueberries (and other plants). Insects, birds, bats, and the wind can transfer pollen from one flower to another. This fertilizes egg cells to produce seeds and fruit.\"},{\"word\":\"pollen\",\"definition\":\"The powdery substance that causes plants to form seeds and fruit.\"},{\"word\":\"fruit set\",\"definition\":\"The process in which flowers become fruit and potential fruit size is determined. The term % fruit set refers to the percentage of flowers which produce fruit.\"},{\"word\":\"honey bees\",\"definition\":\"Honey-producing bees that live in large colonies. Honey bees are often rented by wild blueberry farmers to help native bees, such as bumble bees, with pollination. Because they are not native to North America, honey bees will not fly (or pollinate) when it is too cold or rainy.\"},{\"word\":\"average\",\"definition\":\"A calculated \"central\" value of a set of numbers. To calculate it: add up all the numbers, then divide by how many numbers there are. Also referred to as the mean.\"},{\"word\":\"dot plot\",\"definition\":\"A type of graph that shows each data point as a dot above a number line. Dot plots are good for comparing data values and visualizing the range of a data set.\"},{\"word\":\"time series graph\",\"definition\":\"A graph of repeated measurements taken over regular time intervals. Time series graphs are useful for visualizing how something changes over time. In a time series graph, time is always plotting on the x-axis.\"},{\"word\":\"phenology\",\"definition\":\"Phenology is the study of the timing of seasonal events in plants and animals such as flowering, leafing, hibernation, reproduction, and migration. \"},{\"word\":\"growing season\",\"definition\":\"The time period between the last frost and first frost.\"}]}",
