    "json" : "{\"askForUserDefinition\":false,\"autoShowMediaInPopup\":false,\"showSideBar\":false,\"definitions\":[{\"word\":\"gene\",\"definition\":\"A simplified definition of a gene is a sequence of DNA nucleotides that carries the information for making a protein.\"},{\"word\":\"complementary\",\"definition\":\"Complementary means matching or corresponding. (It's not the same as compliment, spelled with an \"i\", which means saying something admiring or flattering).\"},{\"word\":\"codon\",\"definition\":\"A codon is a group of three nucleotides that codes for an amino acid. Codons are commonly called triplets.\"},{\"word\":\"eukaryotes\",\"definition\":\"Eukaryotes are organisms whose cells have a nucleus.\"},{\"word\":\"DNA\",\"definition\":\"DNA stands for deoxyribonucleic acid.\"},{\"word\":\"RNA\",\"definition\":\"RNA stands for RiboNucleic Acid. \"},{\"word\":\"dna\",\"definition\":\"DNA stands for deoxyribonucleic acid.\"},{\"word\":\"rna\",\"definition\":\"RNA stands for RiboNucleic Acid. \"}]}",
